				<baseName xml:lang="en"> Electricity for solar power </baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">太阳能发电</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Solar electricity; Photovoltaic power</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Solar electricity; Photovoltaic power</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Energy carriers and technologies</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Electricity</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Solar power, also known as solar electricity, refers to the conversion of energy from sunlight into electricity. This can be achieved directly using photovoltaics (PV) or indirectly using concentrated solar power. Solar panels, which are the main component of solar power systems, use the photovoltaic effect to convert light into electric current. Solar cells on the panels capture sunlight and convert it into usable electricity. Solar energy is a renewable and carbon-free source of energy that has the potential to meet all future energy needs if harnessed effectively. The first solar panels were developed in the 1950s, and since then, technology has advanced, allowing for more efficient energy conversion.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">太阳能又称太阳能发电，是指将太阳光的能量转化为电能。这可以通过直接使用光伏技术（PV）或间接使用聚光太阳能来实现。太阳能电池板是太阳能发电系统的主要组成部分，它利用光伏效应将光转换成电流。太阳能电池板上的太阳能电池捕捉阳光，并将其转化为可用的电力。太阳能是一种可再生、无碳的能源，如果得到有效利用，有可能满足未来所有的能源需求。第一块太阳能电池板开发于 20 世纪 50 年代，此后技术不断进步，实现了更高效的能源转换。</common:generalComment>
